# STOP - CRITICAL READING REQUIRED

**THIS FILE MUST BE READ FIRST BY ALL AI AGENTS**

## WHAT IS THIS?

This is the AI manifest for **Session Sentinel** — a multi-AI session health monitor with system tray, self-healing, fault tolerance, self-diagnostics, and PanLL panel integration.

## CANONICAL LOCATIONS (UNIVERSAL RULE)

### Machine-Readable Metadata: `.machine_readable/` ONLY

These 6 a2ml files MUST exist in `.machine_readable/` directory ONLY:
1. **STATE.a2ml** - Project state, progress, blockers
2. **META.a2ml** - Architecture decisions, governance
3. **ECOSYSTEM.a2ml** - Position in ecosystem, relationships
4. **AGENTIC.a2ml** - AI agent interaction patterns
5. **NEUROSYM.a2ml** - Neurosymbolic integration config
6. **PLAYBOOK.a2ml** - Operational runbook

**CRITICAL:** If ANY of these files exist in the root directory, this is an ERROR.

### Source Code Layout

```
session-sentinel/
├── src/core/              # AffineScript (.as) — business logic
│   ├── config.as          # Configuration system + provider definitions
│   ├── scanner.as         # Multi-AI storage scanner
│   ├── health.as          # Health zone classification + trend analysis
│   ├── healer.as          # Self-healing engine
│   ├── diagnostics.as     # Self-diagnostics + watchdog
│   ├── monitor.as         # Main monitoring loop
│   └── providers.as       # AI provider detection + registration
├── src/interface/abi/     # Idris2 — formally verified specifications
│   ├── HealthState.idr    # Health zone state machine with proofs
│   ├── MonitorProtocol.idr # Monitor command/response protocol
│   └── PanelProtocol.idr  # PanLL panel communication protocol
├── src/interface/ffi/     # Zig — native platform integration
│   ├── build.zig          # Build configuration
│   └── src/
│       ├── main.zig       # Entry point + CLI + signal handling
│       ├── tray.zig       # KDE StatusNotifierItem (system tray)
│       ├── dbus.zig       # DBus abstraction layer
│       ├── icons.zig      # Dynamic SVG icon generation
│       └── watchdog.zig   # Watchdog + fault tolerance
├── src/panels/            # PanLL panel
│   └── manifest.json      # Panel manifest (4 views)
├── config/                # Default configuration
│   └── session-sentinel.toml
└── systemd/               # Boot activation
    ├── session-sentinel.service
    └── install.sh
```

### Language Roles

| Language | Role | Directory |
|----------|------|-----------|
| AffineScript | Core logic (affine types, effects, dependent types) | `src/core/` |
| Idris2 | ABI specifications (proofs, state machines) | `src/interface/abi/` |
| Zig | FFI implementation (system tray, DBus, native) | `src/interface/ffi/` |
| JSON | PanLL panel manifest | `src/panels/` |
| TOML | Configuration | `config/` |

## CORE INVARIANTS

1. **No state file duplication** — Root must NOT contain STATE.a2ml, META.a2ml, etc.
2. **Single source of truth** — `.machine_readable/` is authoritative
3. **License consistency** — All code PMPL-1.0-or-later
4. **Author attribution** — Always "Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>"
5. **Container images** — MUST use Chainguard base
6. **Container runtime** — Podman, never Docker. Files are `Containerfile`, never `Dockerfile`
7. **No banned patterns** — No believe_me, assert_total, sorry, unsafeCoerce in any language
8. **Multi-AI design** — All features work for any AI provider, not just Claude
9. **Proven alternatives** — Check proven-servers for formally verified alternatives before writing new code
10. **Panels not panes** — PanLL uses "panels", never "panes"

